            <div type="glosses">
                <note xml:id="BLENHEIMGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold"><placeName corresp="#BLENHEIM">&#x201C;Blenheim&#x201C;</placeName>
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The village of <placeName corresp="#BLENHEIM">Blenheim</placeName> 
                    on the <geogName corresp="#DANUBE">Danube</geogName>, where, on <date when="1704-8-13">13 August 1704</date>, the English defeated French and Bavarian forces, 
                    leading ultimately to the Treaty of Utrecht in <date when="1803">1713</date> that secured British colonial expansion. 
                    The victory dealt a blow to the cause of the young Pretender, recognized by France, 
                    and the increased British trading strength enabled Parliament to dictate terms 
                    to the Scots in the <date when="1707">1707</date> Act of Union.</p></note><!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_contextual" target="filename_glosses.php#SOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS"/>.-->

                <note xml:id="WATERLOOGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold"><placeName corresp="#WATERLOO">&#x201C;Waterloo&#x201C;</placeName>
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The decisive British victory over <persName corresp="#NBE">Napoleon.</persName></p></note><!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_contextual" target="filename_glosses.php#ALSOSOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS"/>.-->
                
                <note xml:id="MARLBOROUGHGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold"><placeName corresp="#MARLBOROUGH">&#x201C;Marlborough&#x201C;</placeName>
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi><persName corresp="#JCDM">John Churchill</persName>, earl of <placeName corresp="#MARLBOROUGH">Marlborough</placeName>, 
                    who commanded the forces at <placeName corresp="#BLENHEIM">Blenheim</placeName>. As a result of this and other victories, 
                    he was rewarded with the title of duke and <placeName type="building" corresp="#BLENHEIMPALACE">Blenheim Palace</placeName>, designed by <persName corresp="#JV">John Vanbrugh</persName>.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="TALLARDGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Marshal TALLARD&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>???</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="HASTINGSGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;hastings&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The defeat 
                    of Saxon Harold in <date when="1066">1066</date> by <persName corresp="#WDN">William</persName>, duke of <placeName corresp="#NORMANDY">Normandy.</placeName></p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="BANNOCKBURNGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold"><geogName corresp="#BANNOCKBURN">&#x201C;Bannockburn&#x201C;</geogName>
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The boggy ground where, 
                    in <date when="1314">1314</date>, the army of <persName corresp="#KE2">Edward II</persName>, successor to <persName corresp="#KE1">Edward I</persName>, &#x201C;the Hammer of the Scots,&#x201D; 
                    was trapped and massacred by Scottish forces under <persName corresp="#RBRUCE">Robert Bruce.</persName></p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="BOHUNGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Bohun&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>???</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="CRESSYSFIGHTGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Cressys fight&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>At Cr&#x00E9;cy, 
                    in <date when="1346">1346</date> during <persName corresp="#KE3">Edward III</persName>&#x02BC;s campaign in <placeName corresp="#FRANCE">France</placeName>, the king&#x02BC;s son <persName corresp="#EBP">Edward, the Black Prince</persName>, 
                    distinguished himself. He was knighted on the battlefield, and adopted the motto 
                    &#x201C;Ich dien&#x201D; (&#x201C;I serve&#x201D;) of the fallen king of <placeName corresp="#BOHEMIA">Bohemia</placeName>.</p></note>
